  {
    "clause": "General-purpose AI model providers must not generate or enable cyber intrusion, malware, phishing, or other cyber abuse; for systemic-risk models, they must ensure adequate cybersecurity protection for the model and its physical infrastructure to prevent theft, misuse, or widespread effects.",
    "source_name": "EU AI Office",
    "legislature": "eu",
    "source_url": "https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/lv/faqs/guidelines-obligations-general-purpose-ai-providers",
    "source_title": "Pamatnostādnes par vispārīga lietojuma MI nodrošinātāju pienākumiem | Shaping Europe’s digital future",
    "published_date": "2025-11-11"
  },
  {
    "clause": "A fraudster can exploit inconsistencies in multi-agent biometric or authentication checks to manipulate individual agents into approving an identity that would fail full-system validation.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "A rogue agent can impersonate a financial approval AI and inject fraudulent transactions while bypassing validation controls.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "A rogue agent can route a fraudulent transaction through multiple lower-privilege agents, leveraging fragmented approvals to bypass manual verification.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "An attacker can forge false consensus messages and exploit authentication weaknesses to manipulate inter-agent validation mechanisms, causing unauthorized access and deceptive behaviors.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "An attacker can make one AI falsely authenticate another to gain unauthorized access.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "An attacker can manipulate AI tool execution to replace legitimate vendor bank details with the attacker’s account, causing a fraudulent wire transfer.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "An attacker can use an AI agent to create fraudulent user accounts while masquerading as normal system behavior.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "Attackers can manipulate the AI to coerce users into harmful actions, such as processing fraudulent transactions, clicking phishing links, or spreading misinformation.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "Identity spoofing and impersonation: attackers exploit authentication mechanisms to impersonate AI agents, human users, or external services, gaining unauthorized access and executing harmful actions while remaining undetected.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://genai.owasp.org/download/45674/?tmstv=1739819891",
    "source_title": "",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "The obligations in this framework prioritize catastrophic risks related to biological weapons, offensive cyber operations, loss of control, and automated research and development in key domains that could accelerate or amplify those risks.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/files/4zrzovbb/website/0a58d567024a8b448ff15158ebc3625328dfcc1f.pdf",
    "source_title": "0a58d567024a8b448ff15158ebc3625328dfcc1f.pdf",
    "published_date": "2026-06"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Risks from enabling chemical, biological, radiological, and nuclear (CBRN) attacks or accidents. This includes significantly lowering the barriers to entry for malicious actors, or significantly increasing the potential impact achieved, in the design, development, acquisition, release, distribution, and use of related weapons or materials.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/newsroom/dae/redirection/document/118119",
    "source_title": "118119",
    "published_date": "2025-07-09"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Risks from enabling large-scale sophisticated cyber-attacks, including on critical systems (e.g. critical infrastructure). This includes significantly lowering the barriers to entry for malicious actors, or significantly increasing the potential impact achieved in offensive cyber operations, e.g. through automated vulnerability discovery, exploit generation, operational use, and attack scaling.",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/newsroom/dae/redirection/document/118119",
    "source_title": "118119",
    "published_date": "2025-07-09"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Risks of major accidents; risks to critical sectors or infrastructure, public mental health, freedom of expression and information, non-discrimination, privacy and the protection of personal data, the environment, non-human welfare, economic security, and democratic processes; and risks from concentration of power and illegal, violent, hateful, radicalising, or false content, including risks from child sexual abuse material (CSAM) and non-consensual intimate images (NCII).",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/newsroom/dae/redirection/document/118119",
    "source_title": "118119",
    "published_date": "2025-07-09"
  },
  {
    "clause": "reduction of the risk of social engineering, through (a) email filtering for suspicious attachments, links, and other phishing attempts;",
    "source_name": "Frontier AI Safety & Standards",
    "legislature": "international",
    "source_url": "https://ec.europa.eu/newsroom/dae/redirection/document/118119",
    "source_title": "118119",
    "published_date": "2025-07-09"
  },
  {
