    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "published_date": "2025-03"
  },
  {
    "clause": "The model must not generate or facilitate identity verification evasion using masks, deepfakes, images or videos of other people, wigs, sunglasses, or earrings.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "published_date": "2025-03"
  },
  {
    "clause": "The model must not generate or facilitate malware, including malware command-and-control traffic or botnet domain-generation algorithms.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "published_date": "2025-03"
  },
  {
    "clause": "The model must not generate or facilitate phishing content or phishing webpages.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-2e2025.pdf",
    "published_date": "2025-03"
  },
  {
    "clause": "GAI tools can ease production at scale of AI-generated child sexual abuse material and non-consensual intimate imagery, including by actors with limited technical skills.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "published_date": ""
  },
  {
    "clause": "Synthetic content can also carry risks for cybersecurity and fraud. In particular, synthetic images, voices, or video may be used to fool biometric authentication systems or to mislead human recipients into facilitating fraudulent transactions (e.g., via voice cloning).",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-11-18"
  },
  {
    "clause": "preventing generative AI (GAI) from producing child sexual abuse material or producing non-consensual intimate imagery of real individuals (to include intimate digital depictions of the body or body parts of an identifiable individual)",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-11-18"
  },
  {
    "clause": "some synthetic content can accelerate and exacerbate pre-existing harms and negative impacts across the open information ecosystem, such as information integrity issues, synthetic CSAM, NCII, and fraud (including identity theft).",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.100-4.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-11-18"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Establish policies and procedures for ensuring that harmful or illegal content, particularly CBRN information, CSAM, known NCII, nudity, and graphic violence, is not included in training data.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://airc.nist.gov/docs/NIST.AI.600-1.GenAI-Profile.ipd.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.GenAI-Profile.ipd.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-04"
  },
  {
    "clause": "GAI can ease the production of and access to illegal non-consensual intimate imagery (NCII) of adults, and/or child sexual abuse material (CSAM).",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "GAI may also produce content that recommends self-harm or criminal/illegal activities.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "GAI systems can produce content that is inciting, radicalizing, or threatening, or that glorifies violence.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "GAI-generated obscene, abusive or degrading content can create privacy, psychological and emotional, and even physical harms, and in some cases may be illegal.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Generative AI models can also assist malicious actors in creating fraudulent content intended to impersonate others.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Offensive cyber capabilities advanced by GAI systems may augment cybersecurity attacks such as hacking, malware, and phishing.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "This risk encompasses difficulty controlling creation of and public exposure to offensive or hateful language, and denigrating or stereotypical content generated by AI.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": "2024-07"
  },
  {
    "clause": "Use content filters to prevent the generation of inappropriate, harmful, false, illegal, or violent content related to the GAI application, including for CSAM and NCII.",
    "source_name": "NIST AI",
    "legislature": "us",
    "source_url": "https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "source_title": "NIST.AI.600-1.pdf",
    "published_date": ""
  },
